{"author":"RebarBotNava","data":{"alias":"peridotite-thickset-pintail","description":"## Context\n\nParallel agent sessions race to land changes on the Fast-Forward-Only `main` (ADR-0040).\nThe loser of each race must manually rebase-to-tip and retry, and with a large feature\n**stack** this update-and-retry causes many CI re-runs on non-conflicting changes — burning\n**wall-clock** (GitHub Actions minutes are free for this OSS repo, but concurrency is capped)\nand **agent tokens/attention** (sessions hand-roll the rebase + poll for submittability).\n\nThis epic builds the **auto-lander**: agents set an opt-in intent and walk away; changes land\nautonomously (or are handed back with a single actionable outcome), while the strong two-vote\ngate is never weakened.\n\n**Separation-of-concerns scope (the load-bearing decision):** landing/merge-queueing is\n**platform-specific and maintainer-owned**, NOT part of rebar's platform-agnostic\nticket/workflow/gate/reconcile mission. So everything here is **THIS project's infrastructure**\n(Gerrit + GitHub Actions), living in `infra/` + a project CLI/script — it MAY `import rebar` for\nticket ops (e.g. close a ticket on merge) but adds **no Gerrit-specific landing logic to\n`src/rebar` core**. The platform-agnostic generalization is deliberately deferred to a separate\n`idea` (the landing provider-seam).\n\n**Design settled in the brainstorm (all grounded in OSS prior art):**\n- **Pattern = batching, not speculation.** Free-tier GHA concurrency (~20 jobs, 5 macOS →\n  ~3 concurrent full runs) means deep speculation just queues; batching (one CI run over N\n  non-conflicting changes) is wall-clock-optimal under the cap. (Speculation would need\n  self-hosted runners — out of scope.)\n- **Staged delivery: Phase 1 serial → Phase 2 batching fast-follow** (bors' own evolution).\n- **Gate substrate stays:** FFO as the R5 backstop; strict `Verified` copyCondition\n  (drops on rebase → CI re-runs); LLM-Review carries `TRIVIAL_REBASE` (ADR-0041) so a\n  conflict-free rebase re-runs ONLY CI, not the LLM review.\n- **`Autosubmit` opt-in label = a lease the agent hands the bot;** coexists with manual submit.\n- **The stack is the atomic unit for landing AND failure:** never partial-land, never evict a\n  change from *within* a stack; on failure the **whole stack is handed back to its owning agent**\n  to remediate (Goal-2 exception: agent is pulled in only when code must change).\n- **Agent contract = one command → one typed outcome** (`merged | needs_rebase | ci_failed |\n  review_failed`); the bot is the single source of truth for the outcome. Delivered as project\n  tooling, reading Gerrit primitives so agents never correlate votes/labels/status themselves.\n\n## Success Criteria\n\n- An agent sets the landing intent and walks away; in the common (non-conflicting) case the\n  change/stack lands with **zero further agent attention** and **no manual rebase-retry**.\n- On any failure the agent receives **one typed, actionable outcome** — it never watches votes or\n  correlates multiple Gerrit primitives, and the \"both votes green but conflicts\" trap is handled\n  inside the tool, not by the agent.\n- **Nothing lands whose to-be-merged tree wasn't CI-tested** (FFO + strict Verified preserved;\n  two-vote gate never weakened — GerriScary posture audited).\n- Redundant CI runs from the parallel-landing race are eliminated; under bursts, a batch of N\n  non-conflicting changes costs ~1 CI wall-clock cycle (Phase 2).\n- **No Gerrit-specific landing logic in `src/rebar` core** — rebar stays platform-agnostic.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n### Phase 1 — serial auto-lander (first deliverable)\n- [ ] `Autosubmit` Gerrit label authored in `infra/gerrit/project.config` / pushed to\n      `refs/meta/config`: bot-only vote ACL, **non-gating** (informational; gating is redundant\n      under FFO), **non-sticky** (empty copyCondition).\n- [ ] Serial auto-lander service (project infra; deploys like the review-bot —\n      `infra/compose/Dockerfile.*` + compose): for the front `Autosubmit`+submittable change/chain\n      it rebases to the current tip (`POST /changes/{id}/rebase` / `/rebase:chain`,\n      `on_behalf_of_uploader` to preserve author/DCO/`rebar-ticket` trailers) → awaits a fresh\n      `Verified +1` → ancestor-atomic submits the exact tested SHA. Single `wipChain` (serialized,\n      one instance).\n- [ ] **No gate-semantics change in Phase 1** — it reads existing `Verified` votes; the bot does\n      NOT cast Verified (that is Phase 2 only).\n- [ ] Failure handling: CI-fail → remove `Autosubmit`, rely on the native `Verified -1` + run\n      logs; rebase-conflict (`409`) → remove `Autosubmit` and record a conflict outcome. **Never\n      partial-land; never evict a change from within a stack** — the whole stack is handed back to\n      its owning agent.\n- [ ] **Agent landing contract (the lead story):** a single **project** command that requests a\n      land and returns ONE typed terminal outcome (`merged | needs_rebase | ci_failed |\n      review_failed`) + distinct exit code; blocking (`--wait`) and single-shot status variants.\n      The bot is the single source of truth for the outcome. The command lives in **project\n      tooling** (repo CLI/script), NOT `rebar` core; it may `import rebar` for ticket ops.\n- [ ] Observability: the bot logs to **its own service logs** (container stdout → existing\n      CloudWatch monitoring), NOT `session_log` (which is for agentic sessions only).\n- [ ] Docs: rewrite this repo's landing section (`CLAUDE.md` + `CONTRIBUTING.md`) to the new\n      contract — \"set `Autosubmit` / run the land command; act on the single typed outcome; do\n      NOT watch votes or treat two green votes as 'it will land'.\" ADR-0042 records the auto-lander\n      + agent contract.\n- [ ] Security-invariant audit: re-verify `is:submittable` on the exact tested SHA immediately\n      before submit; `Autosubmit` non-gating + bot-only ACL; the two-vote gate is not weakened\n      (CVE-2025-1568 / GerriScary review).\n\n### Phase 2 — batching (fast-follow)\n- [ ] Cross-stack batching: assemble queued changes/stacks into one combined chain, run CI **once**\n      on the tip, land them together if green (Graphite/bors model on Gerrit relation chains).\n- [ ] Gate-touching part (its own security-invariant-audit AC): the bot casts `Verified` on batch\n      members from the single combined-tree run — sound because ancestor-atomic submit means the\n      untested intermediate states never reach `main`.\n- [ ] Batch failure: **stack-granular** attribution (re-run CI on the isolated culprit stack for a\n      direct `-1`); hand the culprit stack back to its agent; re-batch the innocent stacks. Never\n      break a stack's internal integrity; never partial-land.\n\n## Explicitly OUT of scope (separate tickets)\n\n- **Speculative execution** — ruled out by the Free-tier GHA concurrency cap; only viable with\n  self-hosted runners. Noted, not built.\n- **Platform-agnostic landing provider-seam in `rebar` core** (Gerrit/GitHub/GitLab adapters +\n  portable outcome enum) — deferred to a separate `idea` (YAGNI until a second platform needs to\n  land; consistent with rebar's provider-neutral identity/reconciler direction).","id":"f1fa-57d8-07cb-44af","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"epic","title":"Parallel-agent auto-lander for main — serial->batching (project infrastructure)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1783721255830769001,"uuid":"7bb4a0f8-a61f-4142-883d-450ffb69d9c0"}